luxurious Dharmawangsa Hotel is a tribute to what remains of
Indonesia's conspicuous wealth. Built as an urban refuge for the
country's oil barons, it has private suites with built-in saunas, a
lounge serving cognac and cigars, and a spacious gym where
Indonesia's repo man, Eko Budianto, can be found on a treadmill
each morning, getting in shape to go after some of Indonesia's
wealthiest people. By Wayne Arnold.
