<P>
   All columns have moved, in the commentary (k) category. If you
have questions or need a resend, please call CoxNet, the Cox News
Service, at 404 526-5456.
</P>
<P>
   MCCARTY-COLUMN _ DAYTON, Ohio _ It was the week before our 25th
high school reunion, and the e-mails poured in like distress
signals from a sinking ship. ``It's the last week before this
reunion thing and panic is setting in,'' wrote my friend Janet.
``The letter said the Saturday night thing would include `games'?
What do they mean by this? Trivial Pursuit? The kinds of idiotic
games one plays at Tupperware parties? Who can name the high school
football team members? Also, what does one wear? Helphelphelphelp
.'' I tried to reassure her there would be no such horrors as high
school Jeopardy. The e-mails came anyway. (McCarty, Dayton Daily
News) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   BASS-COLUMN - I was curious about why Jacqueline Kennedy
Onassis, the editor for my biography of Judge Frank M. Johnson Jr.,
felt so intensely about him. When I asked how she became
interested, she leaned back reflectively at her desk at Doubleday,
then said, ``He's long been a hero of mine. I guess it goes back to
the White House and hearing Jack and Bobby talk about him.'' (Bass,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution guest columnist) MOVED.
</P>
