<P>
   LIFESTYLE
</P>
<P>
   NEWS-QUESTIONS _ Q&AMP;A on the news, in two takes. (Bessonnette,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution) (l, a) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   COXNET-WRESTLING
</P>
<P>
   The weekly CoxNet wrestling page is available Wednesday
afternoons by 5 p.m. Keying to the Monday wrestling events, It's
good for publication any day through Sunday. Here are the elements
on the page, which are also moving on the entertainment wire:
</P>
<P>
   WRESTLING-FEATURE _ A feature on a wrestler or issue. This week:
(Cox News Service) WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   WRESTLING-COLUMN _ Our columnist John Allen writes about a trend
or issue in pro wrestling. This week: (Allen, Cox News Service)
</P>
<P>
   WRESTLING-GRAPEVINE _ News and gossip from the wrestling world.
(Allen, Cox News Service)
</P>
<P>
   WRESTLING-RAIL _ Brief items of interest, including bios, TV
info, etc. (Allen, Cox News Service)
</P>
<P>
   FOOD
</P>
<P>
   COXNET FOOD PAGE
</P>
<P>
   EDS: This is the CoxNet FOOD page for the current week. This
layout is now available.
</P>
<P>
   COXNET FOOD 0724 SWEET LEMONADE _ Lemonade's big secret is a
balancing act between its three essential ingredients: lemons,
water and sweetener. Sounds simple, but striking the perfect spot
between syrupy sweet and startlingly tart may take a bit of
hunting. (Langhenry, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) Art includes a
3-column color photo of a pitcher of lemonade and a 1-column color
photo of a glass of lemonade.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   RECIPES _ Recipes for OId-Fashioned Lemonade, Minted Vodka
Lemonade and Sparkling Strawberry Lemonade.
</P>
<P>
   SPRUCING IT UP: Info box offering tips to spruce up your
lemonade
</P>
<P>
   CYBERSPICE _ To claim the singular taste and intangible energy
of freshly harvested produce is the ultimate reward for the
gardener who loves to cook. (Parham, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
Art includes 2-column color photo of a basket of vegetables.
</P>
<P>
   RECIPE _ Crispy Okra with Basil, Pesto and Bacon.
</P>
<P>
   FOOD-AUGUST _ When we drag in from the steam bath outside, the
last thing we crave is a slow-simmered stew or hot-from-the-oven
roast. We wither at the thought of rich, cheesy casseroles or
cream-laden sauces. And at this stage of summer, we're no longer
thrilled to spend every muggy evening sweating over a hot frill. So
what does whet our appetite? For August, 31 daily recipes to beat
the heat. (Kessler, Langhenry, Morrow, Walker, Puckett, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   FOOD-AUGUST-RECIPES _ Recipe page to go with AUGUST story
centerpieced on AJC weekly food section. (Kessler, Langhenry,
Morrow, Walker, Puckett, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) WITH LAYOUT.
</P>
<P>
   FOOD-RECIPESWAP _A weekly recipe exchange column. This week:
7-flavor poundcake. (Langhenry, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   FOOD-INSEASON _ A weekly column featuring recipes for seasonal
produce. This week: Raspberries. (Hizer, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution freelancer; not for use by New York Times
clients.)
</P>
<P>
   FOOD-SKUBE-BEERCOLUMN _ A weekly beer column by the Michael
Skube of the Atlanta Journal-Constitution. This week: Frech brewing
(Skube, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   FOOD-VERSATILEVEGETARIAN - A weekly column featuring vegetarian
recipes. This week: Vegetarian barbecue. (Hizer, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution freelancer; not for use by New York Times
clients.)
</P>
<P>
   FOOD-CYBERSPICE _ A weekly column looking at the plethora of
recipes on the Internet. (Parham, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   RANCH _ AUSTIN, Texas _ Ranch dressing was begun on a ranch in
California, but Texans have embraced it as their own. So has the
rest of the country. As it celebrates its 25 years in national
distribution this year, it is now the No. 1 dressing. But it is
more than just a buttermilk salad dressing. It is a flavor for
chips, chex mix, potatoes, soups, as well as a dunking sauce for
pizza. (Crider, Austin American-Statesman) WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   CHERRY-TOMATOES _ At this point in the summer season, the cherry
tomatoes ripen in waves. Vines are weighted down with fat clusters,
begging to be pulled off by the handful. Mostly they end up being
eaten like a snack. But there are other ways to put this abundance
to good _ and very easy _ use. (Dayton Daily News). WITH PHOTOS.
MOVED. WITH CHERRYTOMATO-RECIPES _ Recipes for cherry tomatoes.
(Dayton Daily News) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   CHERRYTOMATO-TIPS_ Tips for hollowing out cherry tomatoes.
(Dayton Daily News) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   ENTERTAINMENT-ARTS
</P>
<P>
   TVTOUR-ABC2 _ PASADENA, Calif. _ News and notes from second day
of ABC's presentation. (Jubera, Atlanta journal-Constitution). 28.
</P>
<P>
   TV-GUMBLE _ TV Columnist Kevin Thompson talks about Bryant
Gumbles move to the early morning. (Thompson, Palm Beach Post). 30.
WITH LAYOUT.
</P>
<P>
   WARPEDTOUR _ An advance of the Warped Tour at Lakewood
Amphitheatre on Thursday 7/29. Tour features a lineup that ranges
from metal to funk (Eminem, Pennywise, Blink 182, Ice T) that
appeals to preteens, teens and those in their early 20s, primarily
young, aggressive males. (Harrison, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
20.
</P>
<P>
   VIDEO-OCTOBERSKY _ Main video review: ``October Sky.'' (Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   VIDEO-MINIS _ Mini views of new videos: ``Payback,'' ``Baby
Geniuses,'' ``Blast from the Past,'' ``Noah's Ark'' and ``La
Stentinelle.'' (Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   VIDEO-RINGEL _ Celebs are often re-paired in films (like
``Pretty Woman's'' Julia Roberts and Richard Gere in the new
``Runaway Bride.'' We talk about other couples like ``Sleeping in
Seattle's'' Tom Hanks and Meg Ryan who later appeared in ``You've
Got Mail.'' (Ringel, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 22
</P>
<P>
   VIDEO-NEXT _ Upcoming videos: ``Cruel Intentions,'' ``Message in
a Bottle,'' ``Tango'' and ``20 Dates.'' (Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 10.
</P>
<P>
   AUDIO-PANIC _ Lede record review of Widespread Panic. (Hamilton,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   AUDIO-MINIS _ Mini reviews of new albums from Incognito, Too
Short and Willie Nelson. (Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   AUDIO-COUNTRY/RAP/POP _ Review of new album by Townes Van Zandt.
(MLongino, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 6.
</P>
<P>
   COXNET BUDGET INFORMATION
</P>
<P>
   So specialty editors can focus on one day's budget, CoxNet
produces themed features budgets each day. Here is the schedule:
</P>
<P>
   Monday for Tuesday: Technology
</P>
<P>
   Tuesday for Wednesday: Automotive, personal finance and home &AMP;
garden
</P>
<P>
   TODAY: Food, CD reviews, video reviews
</P>
<P>
   Thursday for Friday: Movie reviews, travel, books and fashion
</P>
<P>
   Friday for Saturday: Religion and science &AMP; health
</P>
<P>
   In addition, separate budgets move daily with spot news, sports,
business and commentary.
</P>
<P>
   Stories are moving in the category they're listed under. Stories
moving to duplicate categories are marked. An ETA is given if a
story will move after 8 p.m. Eastern.
</P>
<P>
   If you have questions or need a resend, please call CoxNet, the
Cox News Service, at 404-526-5456.
</P>
<P>
   THE LAYOUT'S DONE FOR YOU: Stories marked as a CoxNet layout are
available for purchase in paginated form:
www.nytsyn.com/pageexpress.
</P>
