makers and cellar masters.
</P>
<P>
   The high points are tastings and dinners at famed Bordeaux
chateaux, such as Smith Haut-Lafitte and Pichon Lalande. This
eight-day tour is scheduled for October, and the cost is $4,295.
</P>
<P>
   -----
 &UR; Herzerl Tours (127 West 26th St., New York, N.Y. 10001;
800-684-8488; www.herzerltours.com) &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   If Austrian music, wine, food or Christmas celebrations are of
interest, Herzerl probably has a tour to suit.
</P>
<P>
   ``The Sound of Austrian Music with Johann Strauss'' is an
eight-day tour that includes visits to Mozart's birthplace, a
Strauss concert in Vienna, a Haydn concert and a Vienna Boys Choir
performance.
</P>
<P>
   The next departure is September and the cost, which includes
airfare from New York, is $2,575.
</P>
<P>
   -----
 &UR; IST Cultural Tours (225 West 34th St., New York, N.Y. 10122;
800-833-2111) &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   IST Cultural Tours offers classic themed tours in the company of
academic specialists. Their itineraries include France, Italy,
China, Greece, Turkey, Egypt, Israel, Austria, Hungary and the
Czech Republic.
</P>
<P>
   ``Treasures of the Nile'' is a 14-day trip that includes six
nights cruising on the Nile. Cairo, Aswan and Luxor are high
points, all in the company of an Egyptologist.
</P>
<P>
   The next departure is in October. and the cost is $4,415.
</P>
<P>
   For further information, ``The Educated Traveler'' (P.O. Box
220822, Chantilly, Va. 20153; 800-648-5168) is a bimonthly
publication devoted to special interest tours.
</P>
<P>
   The yearly subscription rate of $57 includes a Directory of
Museum-Sponsored Tours and a Directory of Special Interest Travel.
</P>
<P>
   -----
</P>
