<HEADER>
A6817 &Cx1f; ttf-z
r t &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-HONG-KONG-SPECIALS-TR     07-28 1433
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-HONG-KONG-SPECIALS-TRAVEL-NYTSF </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
HONG KONG DEALS ... AND MORE 
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   (To purchase this special ``one-shot'' feature culled from The
New York Times Syndicate's ``Way To Go!'' travel package, contact
New York Times Syndicate Sales Executive Debra Weydert by phone,
(732) 390-4480, or fax, (732) 390-4697.)
</P>
<P>
   &UR; (PLEASE NOTE: This article has been transmitted twice _ into the
``t'' travel news and ``l'' lifestyle news files.) &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   -----------------------FREE ART!-----------------------
</P>
<P>
   One color slide is available FREE by e-mail. Please specify that
you want the art when you order the article.) &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   -------------------------------------------------------
</P>
<P>
   &UR; By ADELE MALOTT &QL; 
 &UR; (Distributed by New York Times Special Features) &LR;  &QC;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; HONG KONG TOURS &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Adventurous seniors ages 60 and older who are planning to visit
Hong Kong in the near future are entitled to some nice discounts _
13 percent to 15 percent off _ on three special tours offered by
the Hong Kong Tourist Association.
</P>
<P>
   For example, the Family Insight tour lets travelers experience a
day in the life of ordinary Hong Kong residents by visiting such
facilities as public housing, a kindergarten or welfare
organization, as well as spending time with a local family. Mature
travelers pay a discounted tour price of $31.
</P>
<P>
   Other tours that feature senior discounts are The Land Between
($45, a 13 percent savings), which travels to areas outside the
city, including Chok Lam Shim Yuen (the Bamboo Forest Monastery); a
bird sanctuary; and rural markets. There's also the Heritage Tour
($37, a 15 percent savings), which stops at the Sam Tung Uk Museum,
an 18th-century walled village and the Man Mo Temple.
</P>
<P>
   Stop by any Hong Kong Information Center and pick up the
``Mature Traveller's Guide,'' which features a Value Plus Card for
discounts at shops and restaurants.
</P>
<P>
   For details about the tours, call (800) 282-4582, or visit the
Hong Kong Tourist Association's Web site at www.hkta.org.
</P>
<P>
   -----
 &UR; NORTH AMERICAN TRAIN DEALS &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Amtrak is touting a 10 percent discount on its Amtrak/VIA North
American Rail Pass for seniors ages 62 and older.
</P>
<P>
   The North American Rail Pass lets a traveler create a custom
itinerary of up to 30 days' travel with unlimited stops. At least
one leg of the trip must be in Canada.
</P>
<P>
   The 10 percent cut is good throughout the year and is applied to
off-peak fares of $450 from Oct. 16 to May 31 and peak fares of
$645, good for travel June 1 to Oct. 15. For more information, call
(800) 872-7245.
</P>
<P>
   Amtrak Vacation packages that include two nights' economy
lodging and passes to some attractions are now available in a dozen
destinations such as Boston, Orlando and the Grand Canyon National
Park in Arizona. Seniors ages 62 and older can apply the standard
Amtrak discount of 15 percent to the packages.
</P>
<P>
   For details, call (800) 321-8684.
</P>
<P>
   -----
 &UR; HAWAII BECKONS &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Hawaii continues to beckon many mature travelers to its lush
beaches with a number of hard-to-beat discounts.
</P>
<P>
   The Ocean Resort Hotel, 175 Paoakalani Ave., in Waikiki takes 55
percent off its value package between now and Christmas Eve. A
standard room that normally rents for $140 is available to those
ages 55 and older for $63 per room per night.
</P>
<P>
   A kitchenette with a regular rate of $150 to $166 goes for $68
to $75 for mature travelers.
</P>
<P>
   For more information, call (800) 367-2317, or visit
www.oceanresort.com on the Web.
</P>
<P>
   The Kona Surf Resort &AMP; Country Club on the Big Island posts a
rate of $129.35 per room per night for those ages 55 and older
until the end of November. These rooms usually rent for $199.
</P>
<P>
   Popular at The Kona Surf are the free Polynesian shows on
Tuesday and Friday nights. For more information, call (800)
367-8011, or visit www.ilhawaii.net/konasurf on the Web.
</P>
<P>
   -----
 &UR; GOLDEN GETAWAYS &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   The Northwoods Resort &AMP; Conference Center in Big Bear Lake,
Calif., which is about 2 1/2 hours east of downtown Los Angeles,
offers two Golden Getaway packages for grandparents and their
grandkids ages 3 to 16. Both packages are good through Sept. 6,
excluding holidays, and are subject to availability.
</P>
<P>
   The first package, priced at $165 per night, Sundays through
Thursdays, includes the choice of a full American breakfast or a
gourmet box lunch to go for four.
</P>
<P>
   The second package on Fridays and Saturdays costs $199 per
night. Activities available for multigeneration groups include
mountain biking, pontoon boat rides, naturalist-guided canoe trips
and trout or bass fishing.
</P>
<P>
   For more information, call (800) 866-3121.
</P>
<P>
   -----
 &UR; RV RESORT DISCOUNTS &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Three resort and RV parks in Oregon and Washington offer
discounts to those ages 55 and older.
</P>
<P>
   The Discovery Point Resort &AMP; RV Park, (541) 271-3443, in
Winchester Bay, Ore., takes 10 percent off its rates _ including RV
campsites with water views that usually rent for $20. They also
have two- and three-bed cottages.
</P>
<P>
   There are 10 percent discounts at the Sunset Resort &AMP; RV Park in
Warrenton, Ore., (503) 861-1760, and Paradise Cove Resort and RV
Park at Castle Rock, Wash., (360) 274-6785.
</P>
<P>
   -----
 &UR; MOUNTAIN ADVENTURE &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Key to the Rockies, a lodging company in Keystone, Colo., posts
20 percent discounts off lodging rack rates for AARP members
through Dec. 25.
</P>
<P>
   For example, a two-bedroom condo that normally rents for $110 in
the fall will cost $88. For more information, call (800) 248-1942
or visit www.keytotherockies.com on the Web.
</P>
<P>
   The company also has created a Mountain Adventure package that
includes four nights' lodging and a choice of recreational
activities _ including bike riding, horseback riding, a gondola
ride, white-water rafting or jeep tour. The cost: from $64 per
person, per night, double occupancy.
</P>
<P>
   -----
 &UR; IRELAND/BRITAIN SAVINGS &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   CIE Tours offers more than 40 escorted trips to Ireland,
Northern Ireland, England, Scotland and Wales that include a $55
per-person discount. It's all part of CIE's ``55 &AMP; Smiling''
program.
</P>
<P>
   The tours are capacity controlled with the discounts going to
the first 15 mature travelers on each departure date.
</P>
<P>
   A typical itinerary is CIE's Irish Tradition, a 12-day coast
trip of Ireland, which includes round-trip airfare from New York,
Newark or Boston, 10 breakfasts and nine dinners, including a
medieval banquet. The trip is regularly priced at $1,918.
Departures run until early October. For more information, call
(800) 243-8687, or visit www.cietours.com on the Web.
</P>
<P>
   -----
 &UR; OUR HEARTS INN &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Mature travelers ages 55 and older can claim a 20 percent
discount at Our Hearts Inn Old Colorado City bed &AMP; breakfast in
Colorado Springs, Colo., near Pike's Peak and the Air Force
Academy. The offer is good throughout the shoulder season of
November to April, except holidays.
</P>
<P>
   Rates range from $85 to $120, depending on the room. For more
information, call (800) 533-7095.
</P>
<P>
   -----
 &UR; NORTH AMERICA NOVOTEL &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Mature travelers who are looking for deep discounts on
accommodations can get up to 50 percent off published rates at the
nine Novotel hotels in the United States and Canada.
</P>
<P>
   For example, the senior room rate is $99 at the Novotel
Meadowlands compared to the regular rate of $169.
</P>
<P>
   Other senior rates during 1999, depending on availability and
exclusive of taxes, are:
</P>
<P>
   _ Novotel Princeton, N.J.: $75 to $99
</P>
<P>
   _ Novotel New York: $189 to $225
</P>
<P>
   _ Novotel Mississauga: $99 Canadian, about $70 U.S.
</P>
<P>
   _ Novotel North York: $99 Canadian, about $65 U.S.
</P>
<P>
   _ Novotel Toronto Airport: $85 Canadian, about $56 U.S.
</P>
<P>
   _ Novotel Toronto Centre: $108 Canadian, about $72 U.S.
</P>
<P>
   The eligibility age for these rates is 55, except for the
Novotel New York (60) and Novotel Montreal Center (65).
</P>
<P>
   For more information, call your travel agent or (800) 668-6835.
 &UR; ----- &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Readers are invited to submit questions and comments to Adele
Malott, c/o The New York Times Syndicate, 122 East 42nd St., 14th
Floor, New York, N.Y. 10168. Send Adele a postcard from your trip
with ideas, questions and information on the bargains you find for
seniors.
</P>
<P>
   Questions may also be sent to Adele by electronic mail. The
address is MatureTrav(at)aol.com. (For (AT) use the symbol on your
keyboard.)
</P>
<P>
   Adele Malott is the publisher of THE MATURE TRAVELER: Travel
Bonanzas for 49ers-Plus, a newsletter for mature travelers.
 &UR; ----- &QL; 
 &UR; Copyright 1999 The Mature Traveler Newsletter &QL; 
 &UR; -0- &QL;
</P>
