<P>
   POISON (Smithville, Mo.): National environmental group charges
Wednesday that the health of infants in Missouri, Kansas, Iowa and
other farm states is at risk because of ground water contamination
by one of the most common farm chemicals, atrazine. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   The group cites many communities, including Smithville, where
infants are exposed to a lifetime's worth of atrazine in their
drinking water. They are calling for a ban on the herbicide, which
could have a huge impact on farming. We get government and industry
response. By Michael Mansur. 25 inches. Story will move in the
