<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-SPECIAL-PHOTO-ADVISORY-NYT </SLUG>
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   KOSOVO BURIALS:
</P>
<P>
   As a NATO helicopter buzzed overhead, hundreds of villagers
mourned 14 Serb farmers killed recently during funeral services on
Wednesday. The men were killed with automatic weapons fire in an
attack Kosovo's Serbs accuse ethnic Albanians of committing.
</P>
<P>
   The following photos, which have moved to photo clients of the
New York Times News Service on Wednesday, July 28, 1999, are
recommended:
</P>
<P>
   (NYT2) GRACKO, Yugoslavia, Serb family members mourn one of 14
Serbs killed recently in the village, 15 miles southwest of
Pristina, the provincial capital of Kosovo, on Wednesday. Some 350
mourners attended the funeral for the 14 men who were killed with
automatic weapons fire in a wheat field near the village. Kosovo's
Serbs accuse ethnic Albanians in the slayings. (Photo by Tyler
Hicks/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   The photo is slugged: KOSOVO-2
</P>
<P>
   (NYT3) GRACKO, Yugoslavia, A British NATO soldier stands guard
as Serbs walk past to a cemetery during a funeral procession on
Wednesday for 14 Serbs killed recently near the village, some 15
miles southwest of Pristina. (Photo by Tyler Hicks/New York Times
Photo)
</P>
<P>
   The photo is slugged: KOSOVO-2
</P>
<P>
   The photos will be part of tonight's New York Times Photo
Package, moving Wednesday, 07/28/99. Photo clients will
automatically receive these photos via AP's PhotoExpress or may
download them from either the Wieck Photo Database in Dallas at
972-392-0888 or from NYTPhotos on Newscom at 305-448-8411.
Non-clients can make individual purchases by calling (888) 603-1036
or 212-556-4204.
</P>
