<SLUG> BC-EDEN-ALTERNATIVE-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
PROGRAM HAS LONG-TERM CARE FACILITIES FOCUSING ON LIFE
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By YVETTE CRAIG 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   FORT WORTH, Texas _ To be human is to care for something.
</P>
<P>
   That simple concept is what Dr. William H. Thomas says will end
loneliness and helplessness among residents of long-term care
facilities.
</P>
<P>
   Thomas, a graduate of Harvard medical school, is on a
coast-to-coast crusade to spread his message about redefining care
for the elderly and the role of caregiving in society.
</P>
<P>
   Tuesday, he visited Fort Worth to address long-term care
providers, nursing home residents and their families.
</P>
<P>
   Thomas said nursing home residents often leave behind their
community, friends and families. Everything they care for may be
gone, he said.
</P>
<P>
   Thomas preaches an approach to long-term care that infuses a
conventional facility with life _ from children to animals to
plants.
</P>
<P>
   The idea is to encourage residents to focus on life instead of
giving up on it.
</P>
<P>
   Thomas' philosophy is known as the Eden Alternative. It started
in one small nursing home and has spread to 150 long-term
facilities across the country.
</P>
<P>
   Terry Thompson, a representative of the long-term care ombudsman
program, applauded Thomas' concept. But he added that many
long-term care facilities and nursing homes already provide a
caring environment.
</P>
<P>
   Nursing homes, assisted living facilities and even a state
hospital are beginning to follow the Eden Alternative.
</P>
<P>
   Susan Farris, administrator of Peachtree Place, a facility in
Weatherford, said she knows firsthand that the concept works.
Peachtree, which has 59 beds, was part of the pioneer Eden program
four years ago.
</P>
<P>
   ``It is a wonderful environment to work at,'' Farris said. ``We
are surrounded by growing things. You feel like you are a part of
life here.''
</P>
<P>
   (Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide
Web: www.star-telegram.com) &QL; 
nn
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-07-28-99 1611EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
