husband of a pregnant woman who is in a coma has obtained a
temporary restraining order preventing a hospital from pulling her
life support, which likely would cause the death of both mother and
child. The woman is 14 weeks pregnant. By RON NISSIMOV.
</P>
<P>
   FETUS-ETHICS (Houston) _ A look at the legal and ethical issues
regarding the battle over a fetus in the womb of woman who may be
brain dead. Medical ethicists say that if the woman is declared
brain dead, the man claiming to be her common-law husband will have
no legal standing to demand she be kept on life support to try to
save the fetus. By RON NISSIMOV.
</P>
