   L I F E S T Y L E &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   CAMP COWBOYS &QL;
</P>
<P>
   WICHITA FALLS, Texas _ So what if it was 105 degrees here at 4
p.m. on Saturday? The devoted will come anyway, thousands a day,
every day for the next four weeks, hoping to get a glimpse of, or
even _ dare they dream _ autographs from, their beloved Dallas
Cowboys. For the second year, the Midwestern State University
campus hosts America's team's summer training camp, a sensational
event that has this otherwise flat, sedate West Texas oil town 112
miles northwest of Fort Worth rolling out red carpets and seeing
green. By JUNE NAYLOR RODRIGUEZ. Story will move in ``l'' lifestyle
category &QL; 
 &QL; 
nn
