bipartisan group of Senators hoping to forge a compromise over tax
cuts, unveiled a $500 billion plan aimed at the middle class and
investors. (700 words.) By Mark Stricherz
</P>
<P>
   MAINE-SHIP. The Portsmouth Naval Shipyard finished $3 million
worth of maintenance on the U.S.S. Helena submarine last year, but
the U.S. Navy still hasn't paid the bill. To make up the difference
before the shipyard's fiscal year ends in October, shipyard workers
are being forced to put in overtime. (600 words.) By Sara Kugler
</P>
<P>
   MARYLAND-SPACE-IMPACT. Proposed budget cuts at NASA will impact
local communities that host NASA research centers, such as the
Goddard center in Maryland. By Jonathan Lipman
</P>
