<HEADLINE>
SHORT ITEMS ON TRAVEL DEALS  
 (FOR RELEASE SUNDAY, AUG. 1) 
</HEADLINE>
   (af)  
 By JANET PIORKO   
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BOTSWANA PACKAGED Acacia Travel, a San Diego company, has a
Botswana package that includes seven nights in deluxe Gametrackers
camps, a night in Johannesburg and air fare from New York for
$3,570 a person, double occupancy, from Sept. 1 to Dec. 11.
(Daytime temperatures can exceed 100 degrees at this time of year.)
</P>
<P>
   Travelers may stay in one, two or three of the camps, which are
operated by Orient-Express Hotels and are situated in Moremi Game
Reserve, Chobe National Park and the Okavango Delta. The cost also
includes game viewing, transfers between camps by light plane and
three meals a day. The camps have overhead fans and electricity.
Departures are on Mondays. Information and reservations: (800)
243-6996. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   AUSTRIAN FARE SALE Austrian Airlines has introduced sale fares
from Kennedy International Airport to 15 destinations in Europe,
including Vienna, Prague, Budapest and St. Petersburg. Tickets must
be purchased by Aug. 4 for trips departing Sept. 5 to Oct. 31.
</P>
<P>
   Fares to Austria are $578 midweek (Monday to Thursday), $628 on
weekends. To Prague, Budapest or Warsaw, prices are $588 and $638;
to St. Petersburg or Moscow, $618 and $668. Taxes are extra.
Reservations: (800) 843-0002. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   CANADA BY CATAMARAN The Charlevoix region of Quebec province is
the destination of a four-night package offered by Skican of
Toronto for $620 a person, double occupancy, including round-trip
air fare from New York to Quebec City on Air Canada. The package
also includes travel by catamaran on the Upper St. Lawrence River
and the Saguenay River and accommodation in Quebec City, Tadoussac,
Ste.-Anne-de-Beaupre, and Pointe-au-Pic.
</P>
<P>
   A Unesco Biosphere Reserve, the region is a major whale-watching
area. The company also has other trips in Quebec, starting at $495
a person for four nights, including air fare, rental car and
lodging. Packages are available through the end of November; the
catamaran stops running Oct. 10, but the trip can be made by rental
car later. Information and reservations: (888) 475-4226. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   TAKEOVER DEAL Inter-Continental Hotels and Resorts, which has
taken over the hotel on Central Park South that was most recently a
Westin and previously a Ritz-Carlton, has a Half-Off New York
weekend package (available Friday through Monday, and also on
Thursday for guests staying through Saturday).
</P>
<P>
   Priced at $199 a night plus tax of 13.25 percent tax and $2 a
room nightly, it affords guests 50 percent off hotel services,
including food and beverage, parking and telephone charges.
</P>
<P>
   The 208-room hotel, now the Central Park Inter-Continental New
York, also has a room-only rate of $199 on weekdays, $179 on
weekends. All programs run through Sept. 12. Reservations: (800)
327-0200.
</P>
</TEXT>
