<HEADLINE>
TEST YOUR LITERARY KNOWLEDGE
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Novels (every one a bestseller in its day), a story collection,
a play, a song, and a classic work of philosophical nonfiction: All
are to be found in this high-altitude challenge. Simply match the
title with its author. You pass with nine correct answers and earn
an A with 12 right. Give yourself an additional point if you
identify correctly the work that prefigured a homespun TV series
that enjoyed great popularity. Answers are on the opposite page.
</P>
<P>
   The literary titles:
</P>
<P>
   1. ``Also the Hills''
</P>
<P>
   2. ``The Big Rock Candy Mountain''
</P>
<P>
   3. ``Cold Mountain''
</P>
<P>
   4. ``February Hill''
</P>
<P>
   5. ``The Fool on the Hill''
</P>
<P>
   6. ``High Tor''
</P>
<P>
   7. ``The Hills Beyond''
</P>
<P>
   8. ``Hungry Hill''
</P>
<P>
   9. ``Look to the Mountain''
</P>
<P>
   10. ``The Magic Mountain''
</P>
<P>
   11. ``The Mountain''
</P>
<P>
   12. ``Mountain Time''
</P>
<P>
   13. ``The Seven Storey Mountain''
</P>
<P>
   14. ``The Shepherd of the Hills''
</P>
<P>
   15. ``Spencer's Mountain''
</P>
<P>
   16. ``The White Tower''
</P>
<P>
   Their variably distinguished authors:
</P>
