<P>
   TEN-STEVENSON _ WINNIPEG, Manitoba _ Alexandra Stevenson, who is
just 18, created quite a stir at Wimbledon earlier this month, when
she came out of nowhere to make it to the semi-finals. An even
bigger bombshell was the revelation that her father _ thanks to an
extra-marital dalliance _ was none other than basketball great
Julius ``Dr. J.'' Erving. Alexandra will compete at the Pan
American Games, beginning today. There is a news conference
featuring her Wednesday, at which time _ for the first time _ among
other things, she will talk about her father and her life since a
Fort Lauderdale newspaper discovered the name of her father.
(Archdeacon, Dayton Daily News).
