   &UR;  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; INTERNATIONAL (i) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   CANYONING-DEATHS (Vienna) _ Canyoning: It's an invigorating
sport that's part white-water rafting, part rappelling. But it has
sent 19 people to their deaths in a Swiss creek. Is canyoning too
extreme? By Thomas W. Haines. 900 words.
</P>
<P>
   BALKANS-SUMMIT (Sarajevo) _ President Clinton readies for his
trip to Sarajevo for a Balkans summit starting Friday, perhaps
focusing on how long peacekeeping forces have had to stay in
Bosnia. By Susan Milligan. 1000 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; WASHINGTON (w) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   SENATE-TAXCUT (Washington) _ A major tax cut could doom the
nation's economic boom, Federal Reserve Chairman Alan Greenspan
warns as the Senate opens a showdown over the largest proposed tax
break in history. By Bob Hohler. 1200 words.
</P>
<P>
   IOWA-FORBES (Washington) _ The credibility of August's Iowa
straw poll of Republican presidential candidates is thrown into
turmoil when the head of the state's Christian Coalition trades
charges with the Steve Forbes campaign about allegations of
vote-buying. By Michael Kranish. 1000 words. (w and a coding)
</P>
<P>
   &UR; NATIONAL (a) &LR;
</P>
<P>
