   GORE-LA-RAZA _ HOUSTON _ Vice President Al Gore makes the
keynote address on the final day of the National Council of La Raza
convention Wednesday. Latinos are a key constituency for Gore's
presidential hopes, and his speech as he invades George W. Bush's
home turf will provide clues to his strategy for retaining their
loyalty. (Shepard, Cox News Service). 30.
</P>
<P>
   With GORE-DATA.
</P>
<P>
   Moving in (w) Washington and (p) politics categories.
</P>
<P>
   GWBUSH-FAITH _ Texas Gov. George W. Bush argues that
``faith-based'' programs can transform lives in ways that
government can't, and he has pushed hard for more ties between
Texas and ``faith-based'' and community groups since 1996. But as
he seeks to take the idea national in his presidential bid, Texas
officials don't have solid empirical evidence on performance and
critics worry about violating the separation of church and state.
While there are many questions, the programs have lots of
supporters because they can provide what government can't:
confidence and faith in oneself. (Greenberger, Austin
American-Statesman).
</P>
<P>
   w/ FAITH-WHAT _ What is ``faith-based''? (Greenberger, Austin
American-Statesman).
