Clinton and his counterparts from more than three dozen countries
gather to map out a blueprint for knitting the region back into the
fabric of south-central Europe. (Deans, Cox News Service). 30.
</P>
<P>
   NOTES: This story can be held to run on Fri., July 30.
</P>
<P>
   FALUN-GONG _ While the Chinese government cracks down on
practitioners of Falun Gong, we talk to Atlanta-area practitioners
of the new meditation sect to find out what it is and what they
think of the crackdown in China. They're not angry about it _
because they're never angry about anything _ but they're very sad
and concerned. About 15 or 20 Atlanta Falun Gongians are in D.C.
right now, protesting in front of the Chinese embassy when they can
get a permit. They say they fear Chinese authorities may even begin
executing practitioners, and that is what their demonstration is
meant to prevent. (Melvin, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 25. WITH
PHOTO.
</P>
