<P>
   LA-ECONOMY (Los Angeles) _ Los Angeles County's economy will
continue growing this year but slow slightly in 2000, according to
a forecast to be released Thursday. Tourism and international trade
will gain strength as Asian economies rebound but concerns are
starting to surface about the quality of jobs being created
locally. By Gregory J. Wilcox. (Will also move in the ``n''
California and ``a'' national news wires.)
</P>
<P>
   BLAIR-WITCH (Los Angeles) _ ``The Blair Witch Project'' will be
put to the test this weekend as the ultra-low-budget horror film
moves from art houses to the nation's multiplexes. ``Blair Witch,''
made on a shoestring $35,000 budget in eight days in the Maryland
wilderness, has set Hollywood on its collective ear by grossing an
astounding $5 million in 10 days at just 31 theaters for Artisan
Entertainment. By Dave McNary.
</P>
<P>
   IHOP-EARNINGS (Glendale, Calif.) _ IHOP is expected to stack up
some appetizing quarterly earnings on Thursday. The Glendale-based
franchiser of the International House of Pancakes chain has had a
strong '99. By Enrique Rivero.
</P>
