 &QL; 
 &QL; 
San Francisco _  &UR; OFF THE WALL  &LR; _ When Alfred Preciado went to
Mexico to visit relatives, he never dreamed he'd find a new line of
work. He gave up a job in the auto industry to import decorative
papier-mache animal figures handmade by a centuries-old method. &QL; 
 &UR; By Karyn Houston &QL;  &LR; 
 &UR; c. 1999 The San Francisco Chronicle &QL;  &LR; 
