SAN FRANCISCO _  DELTA  _ One of the hottest spots for summertime
fun in Northern California is the Sacramento-San Joaquin River
Delta, 1,000 miles of tributaries. With a big social scene full of
boaters and sun worshipers, it's no wonder restaurants have popped
up at just about every marina. &HT;    So what are the best restaurants in the Delta? We found 10
places right on the water with menus ranging from well-prepared
standards like burgers and fries to more upscale options with a
little style.
 &HT;     By Robin Davis  
 c. 1999 The San Francisco Chronicle  
<TEXT>
 &QL; 
SAN FRANCISCO _  &UR; PERSONAL &LR;  _ As Americans opt for quicker solutions
to eating, the answer for many is personal chefs. They arrive,
knives and groceries in hand. Surprisingly, many of these personal
chefs can cook a homemade dinner for less than the cost of a meal
at Denny's.
