<P>
   ``Next year is going to set the political tone for the new
century,'' Richardson said. And with Hispanics expected to become
the largest ethnic minority in the country in the next century, the
next election could be ``the most important in the millennium and
in the history of Latino political development (in the United
States).''
</P>
<P>
   The NCLR's rank-and-file members generally agreed.
</P>
<P>
   ``This election is going to make things happen for Hispanics,''
said Oscar Noriega Jr., 28, a former migrant worker who now heads
the Idaho Migrant Council, a public interest group that helps
migrant workers with health care, child care and education.
</P>
<P>
   ENDIT
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
