<HEADLINE>
FRESHMAN MUST WAIT TO ATTEND USC
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By SCOTT WOLF  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ Sagan Atuatasi, an incoming freshman defensive
tackle, will not attend USC this season because he did not meet the
university's admission requirements.
</P>
<P>
   Atuatasi, who played at Los Alamitos High, met the minimum
academic standards of the NCAA Clearinghouse and scored a 980 on
the Scholastic Assessment Test but did not meet the university's
requirements based on his grade-point average.
</P>
<P>
   He plans to attend Cypress College on a part-time basis this
year, and enroll at USC in the fall of 2000.
</P>
<P>
   Atuatasi is no longer required to attend USC, because his
national letter-of-intent has been voided. But his father, Matthew,
said his son still intends to play for the Trojans.
</P>
<P>
   ``He'll enroll at USC next year,'' Matthew Atuatasi said.
``There were never any other schools he considered besides USC.
</P>
<P>
   ``I wanted him to go to USC right away, but now that they made
this decision, it's best in the long run. He'll get a chance to
bring up his study habits and be a student.''
</P>
<P>
   Atuatasi (6-foot-3, 295 pounds) was considered one of the top
defensive linemen in the West. He had 55 solo tackles and eight
sacks at Los Alamitos last season.
</P>
<P>
   Atuatasi, 17, intended to redshirt his freshman season,
according to his father. Matthew Atuatasi said his son will still
redshirt during the 2000 season.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
