r l &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-KIDS:SHOTS-BACK-TO-SC     07-28 0184
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-KIDS:SHOTS-BACK-TO-SCHOOL-CLASSACTS-NYTSF </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
THE LATEST ON IMMUNIZATIONS 
 FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE 
 FROM THE FORT WORTH STAR-TELEGRAM
</HEADLINE>
  World rights. 
 By JESSAMY BROWN 
 Copyright 1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
 (Distributed by New York Times Special Features) 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Nobody enjoys getting shots at the doctor's office, but health
officials emphasize that immunizations are extremely important for
school-age children.
</P>
<P>
   If you're not up to date with your shots, many states can
prevent you from starting school on time.
</P>
<P>
   If needles make you twitchy, here are some tips to get through
the injection:
</P>
<P>
   _Breathe slowly and deeply to keep yourself relaxed.
</P>
<P>
   _Hold your mom's or dad's hand for support.
</P>
<P>
   _Be honest with the doctor and nurse about your worries.
</P>
<P>
   _Think about something else, like giving yourself a treat
afterward or being at your favorite place.
</P>
<P>
   _Race the nurse to see if you can count to 10 before she
finishes the injection.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &UR; -0- &QL; 
 &UR; Copyright 1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram &QL; 
 &UR; (Distributed by New York Times Special Features) &QL;
</P>
