A7696 &Cx1f; tab-z
r l &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-KIDS:FINANCING-BACK-T     07-28 0308
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-KIDS:FINANCING-BACK-TO-SCHOOL-CLASSACTS-NYTSF </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
THINK AHEAD ABOUT FINANCING COLLEGE 
 FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE 
 FROM THE FORT WORTH STAR-TELEGRAM
</HEADLINE>
  World rights. 
 By JESSAMY BROWN 
 Copyright 1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
 (Distributed by New York Times Special Features) 
<TEXT>
<P>
   OK, so your family hasn't won the lottery. Bills for education
can be paid through financial aid, scholarships and grants (you
don't have to pay these back), loans and work/study programs on
campuses.
</P>
<P>
   Besides getting top grades or being a super athlete, there are
other opportunities to win scholarships.
</P>
<P>
   ``Many students and parents think that scholarships go only to
the most brilliant students, the neediest of the needy or the most
spectacular athletes.'' writes scholarship expert Chris Vuturo in a
news release. But that's ``Not so,'' he says. After doing ``a ton
of research'' as a high school senior, Chris got more than $885,000
in financial aid award offers. Now 27, he's the author of ``The
Scholarship Advisor 1999 Edition.''
</P>
<P>
   Scholarships are available based on such factors as: what you
plan to study, career interest, hobbies/leisure activities, work
experience, athletic ability, minority affiliation, religious
affiliation, disability, gender, military service (yours, your
parents' or your grandparents'), residence and where your parents
work.
</P>
<P>
   The University of North Texas' free booklet for prospective
college students, ``How to Choose the Right College for You,''
lists these tips on financial aid:
</P>
<P>
   _Save your money;
</P>
<P>
   _send forms early;
</P>
<P>
   _proofread your applications because errors will delay the award
process;
</P>
<P>
   _ make a copy in case your information is misplaced.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &UR; -0- &QL; 
 &UR; Copyright 1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram &QL; 
 &UR; (Distributed by New York Times Special Features) &QL;
</P>
