NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR THURSDAY, JULY 29
</HEADLINE>
 Eds.: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Thursday. Days and dates refer to the original article's
transmission by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be
adjusted by NYT clients.)  
(gc) 
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-KOCH-DETECTIVES-NYT (moved on Tuesday, July 27)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Tuesday, July 27,
about private investigators who pose as journalists misidentified
an Internet publication that became the target of one investigator
after it criticized a Hong Kong real estate project. The
publication is Webb-site.com, not Cyberport, the name of the
project.
</P>
<P>
   BC-MEMPHIS-MAYOR-NYT (moved on Monday, July 26)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Monday, July 26,
about the Memphis mayoral race misattributed a quotation in some
copies. It was Marcus Pohlmann, a political science professor at
Rhodes College, not Michael Nelson, another professor at the
college, who said:
</P>
<P>
   ``I still think this is Herenton's race to lose. In the old
days, you often had two strong white candidates, and the black
community was the moderating factor. Now it is the opposite. But I
don't see any white candidate emerging with enough support to beat
a Ford or a Herenton.''
</P>
