<SLUG> BC-FBC-WAC-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
WAC AIMING TO SHOW IT'S A VIABLE CONFERENCE
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By WHIT CANNING 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Western Athletic Conference will conduct its first football
media day in its reduced form Thursday when the eight remaining
members gather at the Harvey Hotel near Dallas/Fort Worth Airport.
</P>
<P>
   The reconstructed league launches itself with new hope, a new
direction, and new problems _ but there is little doubt about the
No. 1 priority of the moment: presenting itself to the world in
some sort of identifiable form.
</P>
<P>
   Or, as Rice athletic director Bobby May put it recently, ``I
think the main thing we need to do is get this eight-team
conference out in front of the public and let people know who we
are. I imagine there are a lot of people out there right now who
are a little confused about it, or who maybe think that the WAC
doesn't exist anymore.''
</P>
<P>
   The WAC exists as a league that includes TCU, SMU, Rice, Tulsa,
UT-El Paso, Fresno State, San Jose State and Hawaii. Nevada is
scheduled to begin competition as a ninth member next season. The
league recently cleared one of its most crucial post-breakup
hurdles by negotiating a television contract with Fox.
</P>
<P>
   It's a little thin on guaranteed revenue, but as commissioner
Karl Benson has said, it offers the one thing the WAC desperately
needs: visibility.
</P>
<P>
   ``It gives us the one thing we need most right now _ an
opportunity to display our product before the public,'' Benson
said. ``Now it's up to us to market it in such a way as to ensure
the future success of the league.''
</P>
<P>
   If a dog-and-cat fight for the league title is any sort of
marketing benefit, the WAC may be sitting on a gold mine. The
preseason favorite, depending on the poll, is TCU, SMU, Rice or
Fresno.
</P>
<P>
   ``I really believe we have a legitimate chance to win the
championship this year,'' SMU coach Mike Cavan said. ``But I think
pretty much everyone else feels the same way.'' nn
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
