<SLUG> BC-FAITH-WHAT-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    What is 'faith-based'?
 &HT;    (EDS: SIDEBAR to GWBUSH-FAITH.)
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Churches and religious organizations and their charitable arms
long have received government contracts to run federal, state and
local programs, particularly social programs. The term
``faith-based'' has become a buzzword for political efforts to
encourage such groups, expand their involvement and remove legal
and bureaucratic barriers. Why not call these programs ``religion
based?'' Faith-based is meant to encompass groups other than
traditional religious organizations.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
